data.content:
noun
plural -downs
[count] American football :a score that is made by carrying the ball over the opponent's goal line or by catching the ball while standing in the end zone
He scored a touchdown.
The quarterback threw a touchdown (pass) to the wide receiver.
They won the game by a touchdown. [=by seven points]
A touchdown is worth six points and is usually followed by a kick that is worth another point.
[count] rugby :the act of scoring points by putting the ball on the ground behind an opponent's goal line
[count, noncount] :the moment when an airplane or spacecraft touches the ground at the end of a flight
What was the plane's speed at touchdown? - see also touch down at 1touch

Danh từ
sự đáp xuống (máy bay)
